---
description: Layered architecture enforcement
alwaysApply: true
---

Use the existing project architecture consistently.

Expected structure:
- src/bot            -> Telegram entrypoints, routers, FSM, admin menu
- src/core           -> domain logic and services
- src/infra/db       -> models, session, repositories
- src/infra/queue    -> celery app and tasks
- src/infra/storage  -> S3 / MinIO
- src/infra/notifications -> delivery channels
- migrations         -> Alembic
- tests              -> test coverage

Rules:
- Handlers should remain thin.
- Service layer owns use-case orchestration.
- Repositories own persistence concerns.
- Infrastructure code should not leak into domain logic more than necessary.
- Database schema changes require migration awareness.
- New async integrations should follow the project’s async style consistently.
- Prefer adding small modules over bloated multi-purpose files.
- Keep imports and dependencies directional:
  bot -> core -> infra abstractions / repos
- Avoid circular dependencies.